	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon6.gif" alt="Cool" border="0" />
				<strong>How to save EQ</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Over the past while I have been viewing all the posts on how EQ is bad in general. [Same sent to SOE for the summit] As many of these were wonderful ideas/problems, I have taken the next step and thought out how some of the worst things could be fixed, without removing the entire PoK ect lol.  So here it is...<br />
<br />
PoK- The bane of role playing and of the sense of vastness we all knew or want to know. A level cap should be introduced on all PoK stones. In order to take a stone to somewhere, you must have a key from talking to an NPC in the city that stone is linked to. Also to get the key you must build up faction with the people of that city, so the NPC will talk to you. [I think warmly or better faction here would be good.] This takes care of some of the faction issues as well as opens up the world to adventure again. If you wish to enter the PoK at all you need to get faction with those of say your home city, and to use it like a hub at all, you would need to get faction with the people of other cities around Norath, AND make the journey at least ONCE to the city to get a key for the stone to/from the PoK. On what level would be required to get the key to PoK, I think 45 because if you are really exploring the planes and not grabbing a free ride from Neriak to Gunthak, then it should really not be a bad thing. <br />
<br />
Quests- Just restating what others have said, we need new quests, lots of quests, for all levels, and with some of them being solo. This is being worked on we are told but, I would like to confirm the task system will be like this. Side note- Remove old quests and revamp lots of zones, people have killed Emperor Crush so many times, why does he still rule the keep? <img src="images/smilies/confused.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Confused" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<br />
Luclin- The only problem I hear of in the forums is the incomplete story line, fix it by hiring more writers, or just asking players what a good story would be, and cut and paste what they say into a new inventive story. [If Luclin is gone in EQ 2, then you do need to continue the story line in any case. <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<br />
GoD/OoW- A solution took a while to think up but here it is. You take OoW and make that the end of this story line, have Morden sacrifice <img src="images/smilies/evil.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Evil" class="inlineimg" />  himself to seal the portal to Norath forever. On this idea the Wayfarers have no faction, and that should change, they should break after Mordens death and have each camp have a different faction than the others. For example you might take sides in a multi camp race to find something in LDoN... <img src="images/smilies/grinyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Grin Yes" class="inlineimg" /> As to GoD, you can make a HUGE number of quests for helping out the destroyed people of the new continent [forgot the spelling] rebuild after suffering for so long. Maybe leave behind some invaders to cause trouble... <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<br />
I leave you with my ideas for a Everquest that will be truly forever, and filled with quests. Most of the early things here can be done in ONE patch, the GoD/OoW thing can be done with the next expansion. If Gem would kindly pass this on to the numerous SOE people he meets/talks with that would help a lot. <img src="images/smilies/grinyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Grin Yes" class="inlineimg" /> If you agree please post, if you have ideas to add please post, and if you hate it, do not post, you are being silly if these do not sound good to you!<br />
<br />
Tiesiaan Troiana<br />
Wizard of the 53rd rank<br />
Worshipper of Ro</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
