		<div>I think EQ should be a dynamic world where everyone should be able to get the full experience.  Maybe not 45 as a level requirment, but in a DYNAMIC world new players should get a good game from the start, not be rushed up to the higher levels where as many others have said people do not know how to do many class defining things. PoK is part of what makes the lower levels less fun. I love task system promised by the way, and hope that it works out to be a wonderful addition. Task system and a MODIFIED, not nerfed PoK would truly bring back the game. As wizards its important to understand that a large number of spells are portals, and holding the power to move people is a huge part of the class, and one of the original reasons I became a wizard. <img src="images/smilies/cool.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Cool" class="inlineimg" /> Many here have said that it is too late, but I do NOT think it is. If you think a level requirment is a nerf, then consider, do the other planes not ask of you 45 or more to enter them? If the PoK is a true plane should it not have the same.  The level and faction thing I talked of earlier is not a nerf, its a simple balance system so a level 1 shaman of Halas can not walk less then 1 minute, and find themselves on Velious. Velious is a long walk and boat ride if you do not have faction with say the dwarves of Velious so can not jump over to Velious. If you NEED to use it you earn it. <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" />  Same rule goes for loot in game, so it should be for such a HUGE advantage.<br />
