		<div>I actually thing it would be good for the PoK stones to work just like flagging does for some of the other PoP zones. (i.e. after killing Aerin Dar, you MUST zone into HoH from behind the dragon to complete your flag)  It wouldn't be so bad to have to click on the actual book in Norrath, see the yellow &quot;you receive a character flag&quot; text, then be able to use that stone from PoK.<br />
<br />
I cannot imagine how you could think this is too hard for a new player to do.<br />
<br />
Back in the old days, when we had to walk to the wizard guild uphill both ways in the deep snow, we didn't have those portal stones.  Heck, I had to wait until level 12 before making the journey from Qeynos to Felwithe, because I wanted to be able to bind myself at key locations along the way.<br />
<br />
The dragon tooth idea from Velious was very good, but poorly implemented.  With the addition of character flags, they can do this much more elegantly.<br />
<br />
(I wouldn't level-restrict the stones, but I would force players to click on the book in Norrath before the corresponding one would work in PoK)</div>
